[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6994,
        "end_time": 9434,
        "text": "It&#39;s a good day to be a pirate."
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 9434,
        "end_time": 11244,
        "text": "Amaro and his four mateys,"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 11244,
        "end_time": 12044,
        "text": "Bart,"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 12044,
        "end_time": 12746,
        "text": "Charlotte,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 12746,
        "end_time": 13514,
        "text": "Daniel,"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 13514,
        "end_time": 14225,
        "text": "and Eliza"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 14225,
        "end_time": 15715,
        "text": "have struck gold:"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 15715,
        "end_time": 18804,
        "text": "a chest with 100 coins."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 18804,
        "end_time": 24584,
        "text": "But now, they must divvy up the booty\naccording to the pirate code."
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 24584,
        "end_time": 29349,
        "text": "As captain, Amaro gets to propose\nhow to distribute the coins."
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 29349,
        "end_time": 32321,
        "text": "Then, each pirate, \nincluding Amaro himself,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 32321,
        "end_time": 36728,
        "text": "gets to vote either yarr or nay."
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 36728,
        "end_time": 42604,
        "text": "If the vote passes, or if there&#39;s a tie,\nthe coins are divided according to plan."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 42604,
        "end_time": 44663,
        "text": "But if the majority votes nay,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 44663,
        "end_time": 46995,
        "text": "Amaro must walk the plank"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 46995,
        "end_time": 50046,
        "text": "and Bart becomes captain."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 50046,
        "end_time": 52854,
        "text": "Then, Bart gets to propose\na new distribution"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 52854,
        "end_time": 56746,
        "text": "and all remaining pirates vote again."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 56746,
        "end_time": 60036,
        "text": "If his plan is rejected,\nhe walks the plank, too,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 60036,
        "end_time": 62245,
        "text": "and Charlotte takes his place."
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 62245,
        "end_time": 63826,
        "text": "This process repeats,"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 63826,
        "end_time": 66988,
        "text": "with the captain&#39;s hat moving to Daniel\nand then Eliza"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 66988,
        "end_time": 72526,
        "text": "until either a proposal is accepted\nor there&#39;s only one pirate left."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 72526,
        "end_time": 78427,
        "text": "Naturally, each pirate wants to stay alive\nwhile getting as much gold as possible."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 78427,
        "end_time": 81759,
        "text": "But being pirates, \nnone of them trust each other,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 81759,
        "end_time": 85107,
        "text": "so they can&#39;t collaborate in advance."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 85107,
        "end_time": 87108,
        "text": "And being blood-thirsty pirates,"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 87108,
        "end_time": 91148,
        "text": "if anyone thinks they&#39;ll end up\nwith the same amount of gold either way,"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 91148,
        "end_time": 96297,
        "text": "they&#39;ll vote to make the captain\nwalk the plank just for fun."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 96297,
        "end_time": 100158,
        "text": "Finally, each pirate is excellent\nat logical deduction"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 100158,
        "end_time": 103368,
        "text": "and knows that the others are, too."
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 103368,
        "end_time": 108287,
        "text": "What distribution should Amaro\npropose to make sure he lives?"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 108287,
        "end_time": 113399,
        "text": "Pause here if you want to figure\nit out for yourself!"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 113399,
        "end_time": 114378,
        "text": "Answer in: 3"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 114378,
        "end_time": 115308,
        "text": "Answer in: 2"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 115308,
        "end_time": 116449,
        "text": "Answer in: 1"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 116449,
        "end_time": 118068,
        "text": "If we follow our intuition,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 118068,
        "end_time": 122798,
        "text": "it seems like Amaro should try to bribe\nthe other pirates with most of the gold"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 122798,
        "end_time": 126170,
        "text": "to increase the chances of his plan\nbeing accepted."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 126170,
        "end_time": 131129,
        "text": "But it turns out he can do\nmuch better than that. Why?"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 131129,
        "end_time": 136570,
        "text": "Like we said, the pirates all know\neach other to be top-notch logicians."
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 136570,
        "end_time": 141069,
        "text": "So when each votes, they won&#39;t just\nbe thinking about the current proposal,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 141069,
        "end_time": 145968,
        "text": "but about all possible outcomes\ndown the line."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 145968,
        "end_time": 148832,
        "text": "And because the rank order is known\nin advance,"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 148832,
        "end_time": 154151,
        "text": "each can accurately predict how the others\nwould vote in any situation"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 154151,
        "end_time": 157801,
        "text": "and adjust their own votes accordingly."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 157801,
        "end_time": 162170,
        "text": "Because Eliza&#39;s last, she has the most\noutcomes to consider,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 162170,
        "end_time": 164989,
        "text": "so let&#39;s start by following \nher thought process."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 164989,
        "end_time": 169431,
        "text": "She&#39;d reason this out by working\nbackwards from the last possible scenario"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 169431,
        "end_time": 173201,
        "text": "with only her and Daniel remaining."
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 173201,
        "end_time": 176701,
        "text": "Daniel would obviously propose\nto keep all the gold"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 176701,
        "end_time": 180471,
        "text": "and Eliza&#39;s one vote would not be\nenough to override him,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 180471,
        "end_time": 185631,
        "text": "so Eliza wants to avoid this situation\nat all costs."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 185631,
        "end_time": 188271,
        "text": "Now we move to the previous decision point"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 188271,
        "end_time": 192560,
        "text": "with three pirates left \nand Charlotte making the proposal."
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 192560,
        "end_time": 196501,
        "text": "Everyone knows that if she&#39;s outvoted,\nthe decision moves to Daniel,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 196501,
        "end_time": 199941,
        "text": "who will then get all the gold\nwhile Eliza gets nothing."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 199941,
        "end_time": 202156,
        "text": "So to secure Eliza&#39;s vote,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 202156,
        "end_time": 207291,
        "text": "Charlotte only needs to offer her\nslightly more than nothing, one coin."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 207291,
        "end_time": 209113,
        "text": "Since this ensures her support,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 209113,
        "end_time": 213821,
        "text": "Charlotte doesn&#39;t need to offer Daniel\nanything at all."
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 213821,
        "end_time": 215713,
        "text": "What if there are four pirates?"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 215713,
        "end_time": 220862,
        "text": "As captain, Bart would still only need\none other vote for his plan to pass."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 220862,
        "end_time": 225342,
        "text": "He knows that Daniel wouldn&#39;t want \nthe decision to pass to Charlotte,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 225342,
        "end_time": 229022,
        "text": "so he would offer Daniel one coin\nfor his support"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 229022,
        "end_time": 232172,
        "text": "with nothing for Charlotte or Eliza."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 232172,
        "end_time": 237543,
        "text": "Now we&#39;re back at the initial vote\nwith all five pirates standing."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 237543,
        "end_time": 239952,
        "text": "Having considered all the other scenarios,"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 239952,
        "end_time": 242423,
        "text": "Amaro knows that if he goes overboard,"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 242423,
        "end_time": 244211,
        "text": "the decision comes down to Bart,"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 244211,
        "end_time": 248102,
        "text": "which would be bad news \nfor Charlotte and Eliza."
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 248102,
        "end_time": 253253,
        "text": "So he offers them one coin each,\nkeeping 98 for himself."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 253253,
        "end_time": 255150,
        "text": "Bart and Daniel vote nay,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 255150,
        "end_time": 259304,
        "text": "but Charlotte and Eliza \ngrudgingly vote yarr"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 259304,
        "end_time": 263414,
        "text": "knowing that the alternative \nwould be worse for them."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 263414,
        "end_time": 267383,
        "text": "The pirate game involves some interesting\nconcepts from game theory."
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 267383,
        "end_time": 270124,
        "text": "One is the concept of common knowledge"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 270124,
        "end_time": 273064,
        "text": "where each person is aware of what\nthe others know"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 273064,
        "end_time": 276407,
        "text": "and uses this to predict their reasoning."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 276407,
        "end_time": 280334,
        "text": "And the final distribution is an example\nof a Nash equilibrium"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 280334,
        "end_time": 283593,
        "text": "where each player knows every other\nplayers&#39; strategy"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 283593,
        "end_time": 286394,
        "text": "and chooses theirs accordingly."
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 286394,
        "end_time": 289355,
        "text": "Even though it may lead to a worse\noutcome for everyone"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 289355,
        "end_time": 290979,
        "text": "than cooperating would,"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 290979,
        "end_time": 296555,
        "text": "no individual player can benefit\nby changing their strategy."
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 296555,
        "end_time": 299826,
        "text": "So it looks like Amaro gets to keep\nmost of the gold,"
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 299826,
        "end_time": 302539,
        "text": "and the other pirates might need\nto find better ways"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 302539,
        "end_time": 305214,
        "text": "to use those impressive logic skills,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 305214,
        "end_time": 308475,
        "text": "like revising this absurd pirate code."
    }
]